text: Henry V (; August 1081/1086 â€” 23 May 1125) was the Holy Roman Emperor from 1111 until his death in 1125. He was succeeded by Lothair of Supplinburg. Henry was the son of Henry IV, Holy Roman Emperor and Bertha of Savoy. He was the last ruler of the Salian dynasty. He married Matilda, daughter of Henry I of England, but they had no children.
